      "side": 1,
      "message": "this all feels a bit hokey:\n\n- the test runner marshals []testing.Test to json\n- run.Local/Remote unmarshals that and copies the tests to []run.TestResult\n- this code copies each result\u0027s test back into this []testing.Test\n\ni don\u0027t see an easy fix, though:\n\n- there\u0027s a bunch of shared code between running and listing tests, to the point where i don\u0027t think it makes sense to have a function that returns []run.TestResult for the former and one that returns []testing.Test for the latter\n- i like the present arrangement (after this CL) of run.Local/Remote not having weird out-of-band behavior when listing instead of running.\n\nat the very least, i should probably update this function to use []*testing.Test instead to avoid some copies, though.",
      "revId": "c75934b1ee26e0a0e24159b290a8eff5dce10304",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
