      "writtenOn": "2018-04-13T21:05:59Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "small enough that it\u0027s probably not worth us talking about. :-)\n\nas a quick benchmark, i added a bit of code to either copy 1000 partially-filled testing.Test structs from a []run.TestResult to a []testing.Test, or to just copy their pointers to a []*testing.Test. on my z840:\n\n  2018/04/13 13:52:26 val took 155.578µs                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          \n  2018/04/13 13:52:26 ptr took 15.07µs\n\nit\u0027s surprising to me, but json-encoding the slice of pointers to a bytes.Buffer is also faster than encoding the slice of values:\n\n  2018/04/13 13:55:38 val encode took 1.802817ms\n  2018/04/13 13:55:38 ptr encode took 1.644739ms\n\ni\u0027ve changed this function to use []*testing.Test internally, since that seems (slightly) unambiguously better than []testing.Test.",
      "parentUuid": "a5f676fd_9cca1efb",
      "revId": "c75934b1ee26e0a0e24159b290a8eff5dce10304",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
